.TH DUPMSG 9 "@PACKAGE_DATE@" "@PACKAGE@-@VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_TITLE@ DDI/DKI"
.\"
.\"
.SH NAME
.B dupmsg, lis_dupmsg
\- duplicate a \fISTREAMS\fR message
.\"
.\"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.B #include <sys/stream.h>
.HP 8
.BI "mblk_t *dupmsg(mblk_t *" mp );
.\"
.\"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.PP
.TP
.I mp
the message chain to duplicate.
.\"
.\"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.BR dupmsg ()
duplicates all of the message blocks of a message, keeping the same data
blocks.
The data blocks are reused.  Each data block will have its reference counter
incremented.  If one duplicate message alters the data in a data block, the
change affects all duplicate messages.
.\"
.\"
.SH RETURN
.PP
Upon success,
.BR dupmsg ()
returns a pointer to the duplicate message.
.PP
Upon failure,
.BR dupmsg ()
returns
.BR NULL .
.\"
.\"
.SH ERRORS
.PP
When
.BR dupmsg ()
fails it returns
.BR NULL .
.BR dupmsg ()
fails when the passed in message pointer
.I mp
is
.BR NULL ;
or an allocation failure occurs ona message block while duplicating.
.PP
Normally, if
.BR dupmsg ()
fails and
.I mp
is not
.BR NULL ,
.BR esbbcall(9) 
should be called with the
.I priority
associated with the message for which duplication failed.
.\"
.\"
.SH CONTEXT
.PP
.BR dupmsg ()
can be called from any context, including user context, module procedures,
callouts, callbacks, soft interrupts and interrupt service routines.
.\"
.\"
.SH MP-STREAMS
.PP
.BR dupmsg ()
is MP-safe.
.\"
.\"
.SH NOTICES
.PP
.B LiS
.[
LiS
.]
implements
.BR dupmsg ()
as a looping call to
.BR dupb (9).
One call is to
.BR dupb (9)
is made for each message block.  If
.BR dupb (9)
fails, the partially duplicated message is freed using
.BR freemsg (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.PP
.BR dupb (9),
.BR copyb (9),
.BR copymsg (9),
.BR freemsg (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH BUGS
.PP
.B LiS
.[
LiS
.]
used to have some problems serializing access to the reference count in data
blocks which caused inconsistencies in the reference count when duplicate
messages were freed.
.\"
.\"
.SH COMPATIBILITY
.PP
.BR dupmsg ()
is compatible with LiS
.[
LiS
.]
with the following exceptions:
.IP \(em \w'\(em\(em'u
When
.BR dupmsg ()
is passed a
.B NULL
.I mp
pointer, the results are undefined.  When LiS
.BR dupmsg ()
is passed a
.B NULL
.I mp
pointer, it returns
.BR NULL .
.sp
Portable
.I STREAMS
modules and drivers should not pass
.B NULL
or invalid message block pointers to this function.
.IP \(em
LiS used to have some problems serializing access to the reference count in
data blocks which caused inconsistencies in the reference count when duplicate
messages were freed.
.PP
For a fully functional
.I STREAMS
implementation, use
.BR "Linux Fast-STREAMS" .
.[
LfS
.]
.\"
.\"
